    "body": "> In my Chrome the scrollbar always fades out after a second of inactivity\n\nAha! This is the key. You have the \"show scrollbar only when scrolling\" behavior enabled, and I don't. If I turn that on, I can reproduce it.\n\nThis is either a problem in CodeMirror, or perhaps some of our own CSS getting in its way. Here's [more info](http://marijnhaverbeke.nl/blog/a-pathological-scrolling-model.html) on the shenanigans CodeMirror has to get up to for scrollbars to work properly. It is a frequent source of headaches.\n"
